Liverpool's poor start to the season is down to 'a dark cloud hanging over Anfield'  according to former Reds star John Toshack.

Brendan Rodgers side lost 1-0 to Real Madrid in the Champions League on Tuesday night and have now won just six of their 16 games in all competitions. 

Toshack, who played for the Merseyside club for eight years, believes his old side are struggling for form because they have not yet recovered from narrowly missing out on the Premier League title last term.  

