Ex-Liverpool star John Toshack believes the Reds are still suffering from missing out on the title last season

Rodgers' men lost 2-0 at home to Chelsea on April 27 before throwing away a three-goal lead at Crystal Palace to draw 3-3 with the Eagles just over a week later. 

Those results allowed Manchester City to swoop in and land their second title in three years on the final day of the season, something Toshack feels the Reds have not yet forgotten.

Speaking to BBC Radio 4 on Wednesday, Toshack said: 'I still think there is a hangover there from what happened at Crystal Palace last season, a bitter pill to swallow.

