Asked if the club would finish in the top four this season and get another chance in Europe's elite club competition, Toshack said: 'Well it's still very early with the changes they have made. They have lost a player (Luis Suarez) who is key to everything they did last season and then it's not always easy to replace people like that.

'Maybe people who have come in haven't delivered as quickly as they would have liked.

'They don’t look to be firing on all cylinders at the moment to me.' 

 

